# API Documentation
# api-docs.md

# Lost & Found API Documentation

## Base URL
```
http://localhost:3000/api
```

## Authentication
Most endpoints require authentication using JWT tokens.

### Headers
```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
Content-Type: application/json
```

## Endpoints

### Authentication

#### POST /auth/login
Login with username/password to get JWT token.

**Request:**
```json
{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "message": "Login successful",
  "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
  "user": {
    "id": 1,
    "username": "admin",
    "email": "admin@college.edu",
    "role": "admin"
  }
}
```

### Lost Items

#### GET /lost-items
Get all active lost items with optional filters.

**Query Parameters:**
- `category` - Filter by category (electronics, clothing, accessories, documents, other)
- `found_location` - Filter by location where item was found
- `search` - Search in item name and description
- `date_from` - Start date (YYYY-MM-DD)
- `date_to` - End date (YYYY-MM-DD)
- `sort` - Sort order (newest, oldest)
- `limit` - Number of items to return (default: 50)
- `offset` - Pagination offset (default: 0)

**Example:**
```
GET /lost-items?category=electronics&found_location=library&limit=10
```

#### POST /lost-items
Add a new lost item (requires authentication).

**Request (multipart/form-data):**
```
name: "iPhone 13 Pro"
description: "Black iPhone with cracked screen"
category: "electronics"
found_location: "Library Study Room 3"
collect_location: "Security Office"
notes: "Found under desk"
image: <file upload>
```

#### PUT /lost-items/:id
Update an existing item (requires authentication).

#### DELETE /lost-items/:id
Delete an item (requires authentication).

#### POST /items/:id/collect
Mark an item as collected (requires authentication).

**Request:**
```json
{
  "collected_by_name": "John Smith",
  "collected_by_contact": "john@college.edu",
  "notes": "Verified with student ID"
}
```

### History & Archive

#### GET /history
Get items that have been collected.

#### GET /archive
Get items older than 30 days (automatically archived).

### Statistics

#### GET /stats
Get system statistics (requires authentication).

**Response:**
```json
{
  "summary": {
    "active_items": 15,
    "collected_items": 45,
    "archived_items": 12,
    "total_items": 72,
    "success_rate": 62.5
  },
  "monthly_stats": [...],
  "category_stats": [...],
  "location_stats": [...]
}
```

### AI Assistant

#### POST /ai-assistant
Natural language search using AI assistant.

**Request:**
```json
{
  "query": "Show me phones found in the library this week"
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "query": "Show me phones found in the library this week",
  "response": "I found 2 items matching your query:\n\n1. iPhone 13 Pro - Found at Library Study Room 3\n2. Samsung Galaxy - Found at Library Main Desk",
  "items": [...],
  "search_params": {
    "search": "phone",
    "category": "electronics",
    "found_location": "library"
  }
}
```

## Error Responses

All endpoints return consistent error responses:

```json
{
  "error": "Error message description"
}
```

Common HTTP status codes:
- `400` - Bad Request (validation errors)
- `401` - Unauthorized (missing/invalid token)
- `403` - Forbidden (insufficient permissions)
- `404` - Not Found (resource doesn't exist)
- `429` - Too Many Requests (rate limit exceeded)
- `500` - Internal Server Error

## Rate Limiting

API is rate limited to:
- 100 requests per 15 minutes per IP address
- File uploads limited to 5MB per file

